This paper is primarily focused on learning tractable probabilistic representations, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with computational complexity and algorithms, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses completeness and incompleteness results, which are topics that fall under the sub-category cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper mentions tractability results, which could also place it under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
